      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Domino7337 wrote:</div><div class="orig">I'm rank 9 phys 9 and i just made it to camp drybones. The thistletail marmots here are green (decent challenge) and i haven't been able to beat a single one. I usually spam spirit dart and sacrifice as needed, but when they hit me for 1/4 of my health per hit, and heal themselves, it just isnt fair. Am i doing something wrong, do we suck this bad, or do i just fail?</div></div> <br /> <br />From what I remember (and I started in the same place as you) Thistletail Marmots can easily be brought down at R9. You just need to spam Phantom Dart between each sacrifice. They have low VIT themselves so your Phantom Dart does decent damage on them so they are not too tough to take down. On a side note to get to Rank 10 and get damnation you will notice an increase in your overall damage output on blue/green mobs. Also if you havent already bought one get a copper scepter for the extra damage (better if you get a decorated one if you can afford).<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179">Loadstone Profile</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649">Thaumaturge Guide</a> <br /> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1229110.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
